body:
Steve Rogers in Endgame

This will have spoilers so don’t read this if you haven’t seen Endgame yet

This has been on my mind since I seen the movie when it came out. When Steve took the Infinity Stones back to the times and place that the Avengers got them from. He decided to stay with Peggy and grow old.

But I don’t think Steve would actually do that. For the last few movies, he’s been all about saving Bucky and getting Bucky back to himself. Now all of a sudden he’s just going to leave Bucky in a time period he isn’t quite familiar with, with people who don’t trust or like him that much.

To me and just doesn’t seem like something Steve would do. I know he loves Peggy but why go through all that fighting with the team and all that searching, plus even dropping the shield in front of Tony for Bucky, just to end up leaving him alone.

Am I the only one who thinks this?

summary: I may not have the skill to write down fics doesn't mean i don't think of plenty and when a show ends i just make up an AU with...
body:
I may not have the skill to write down fics doesn’t mean i don’t think of plenty and when a show ends i just make up an AU with just one little thing different in my mind and run with it whenever i daydream about that

What I’m saying is tony got extremis after coming back from titan and that was enough for him to survive snapping also i have a scenario where he uses it to carry JARVIS with him from 2012 to the future but that’s beside the point
